2) Evaluation of candidates in light of that preference:
- Frontiers (Classic Rock; Album-Oriented Rock/AOR): AOR by definition emphasizes the album as a coherent listening unit. Classic rock/AOR records tend to feature layered instrumentation, extended arrangements or instrumental passages, careful sequencing, and production choices that reward sustained, attentive listening (dynamics, stereo staging, textural detail). Those are exactly the kinds of attributes a CD enthusiast who enjoys full-album experiences is likely to appreciate.
