3) Reason for choice and rejection:
I choose Frontiers because its Album-Oriented Rock classification aligns with my explicit enjoyment of listening to CDs as complete works: AOR albums are constructed to be played and appreciated as albums, showcasing production nuance and musicianship across a full running time—attributes that make the CD format worthwhile to an enthusiast. I reject Yes I Am not because it is inferior as music, but because its Pop/Adult Alternative orientation is more single-driven and immediate; that style is better suited to picking out individual tracks than to the kind of cohesive, immersive album listening I value. Thus, Frontiers best matches the listening habits and priorities implied by my self-introduction.

